thread.title: Grain mixed and livestock mixed

title: Grain mixed and livestock mixed
text:
Tip : Use comma (,) to separate multiple quotes. Learn more... 
Thu, Aug 6, 2015, 20:46 BST - UK Markets closed Grain mixed and livestock mixed Wheat and oats higher, corn and soybeans lower on the CBOT; beef higher, pork lower on the CME. Associated Press – 15 minutes ago Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mixed Thursday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was up 5 cents to $5.07 a bushel; December corn fell 2.75 cents to 3.8050 a bushel; December oats rose .75 cent to 2.45 a bushel; while November soybeans lost 10 cents to $9.4325 a bushel. 
Beef rose while pork fell on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was up .68 cent to $1.4885 a pound; August feeder cattle rose .85 cent to $2.1497 a pound; while October lean hogs lost 2.32 cents to $.6445 a pound.
